Menurut saya dan suami hotel ini top markotop abissss. 😊

name: Tiara Surya Bontang Hotel
address: Jln. MT. Haryono No. 56, Bontang 75311 Indonesia

reviews.text: The rooms at this hotel are Large, service from staff hotel is good, located on the side of the road, very easy to reach, the price is also affordable. The facilities at the hotel are quite complete. The rice box breakfast is delicious. Recommended to stay here
reviews.title: Good Hotel in Bontang City

reviews.text:
Stay 2 night at Tiara Surya, Bontang with my family.
The price is affordable, we use deluxe room charged Rp. 325,000 per night.
The room quite spacious, however the condition is quite old. Having trouble finding a electric plug for our phone. 
The bathroom is spacious, good for family with 2 children, have running hot water. 
We experience a knocking wood sound during night, at the morning, we ask the receptionist, they told us that it was the heater machine -can be quite disturbing.
Not much option for breakfast, we have rice and bread.
It have free fast wifi.
The hotel cleanliness is good, the staff is friendly. Choose this hotel if you look for affordable hotel in town for family since it seem the hotel have the policy to accept a known/legal couple.
reviews.title: Not too bad

reviews.text: I usually stay in another hotel each time I come to Bontang for business trip, but this time, I tried to stay here with a suggestion of a client that it's strategically located in the city center. I must say that it was the first and the last time.  The hotel is dark and humid, it definitely looked like a short time/ transit motel.  The room is humid it has no window, the shower is very bad, it flooded the whole bathroom since the floor won't absorbed the water.  The breakfast is very bad and nobody stand by in that "so-called" restaurant, so my colleague and I felt like we were in our house kitchen preparing our own breakfast, very weird.
reviews.title: A big disappointment

reviews.text: Hotel yang sudah lumayan tua. Mau memberikan review yang buruk juga tanggung karena memang hotelnya kelas melati. Kamar sih luas. AC dan TV berfungsi. Ada WiFi yang lumayan ok dan kulkas meskipun tidak dingin. Sarapan tidak istimewa. Saya hanya makan roti dengan mentega. Kalau ingin menarik lebih banyak pengunjung saya sarankan agar mulai membenahi hotel sedikit-sedikit agar tampilannya lebih "fresh". Dengan harga setara, saya rasa di Bontang sudah ada pilihan yang lebih baik.
reviews.title: Seadanya

reviews.text: Letaknya ditengah kota mudah diakses. Kamarnya luas tapi kamar mandi tergantung tergantung harga kamar.. Yang standar ya dapat standar juga kamar mandinya.. Ya namanya juga kelas melati. Tapi mau cari makan diluar mudah sekali, karena banyak tempat makan pilihan dekat hotel.. Untuk sekedar istirahat tidur cukup lah standar hotel ini...
reviews.title: Sesuai standar

reviews.text:
Saya stay 1 malam di hotel ini ketika ada keperluan dinas ke PT Badak NGL
Wowwww, am very surprise!!!! Its a terrible hotel!!

Poin plus:
1. Lokasi strategis di pusat kota bontang, dan dekat dg kawasan PT. BADAK

Poin minus:
1. Kamar kotor dan tak terawat, semacam jarang ditempati dan dibersihkan
2. Pegawai hotel sangat tidak profesional
3. Kamar mandi kotor, air panas dingin tidak berfungsi, shower mati dll.
4. Harga mahal untuk pelayanan yang saya pikir menyedihkan

Dengan berat hati saya sarankan agar anda berpikir ulang sebelum memilih hotel ini. Suatu saat ketika saya kembali ke bontang, saya tidak akan sempat berpikir untuk memilih hotel ini lagi.

Terima kasih
reviews.title: Very Bad!

reviews.text: Letaknya di jalan utama kota Bontang, Kalimantan Timur. Baru masuk sebelah kiri dari arah Samarinda.. Dari luar terlihat kecil dan sempit, tetapi kamarnya lumayan luas dan banyak. ongkos termasuk murah dan terdapat banyak pilihan. Untuk yang deluxpun cukup murah untuk ukuran Bontang.. makan pagi juga lumayan enak .. jadi untuk wisatawan hemat rekomendasi hotel ini deh.. petugasnya juga ramah ramah dan informatif..Tetapi jika dapat kamar di bawah atau atas, bersiap dengan bawaan anda karena tidak ada lift.
reviews.title: mudah di cari

reviews.text: Pertama kali menginjakkan Kota Bontang, nyari penginapan di tengah Kota, dan akhirnya nginap di Tiara Surya Bontang Hotel. Secara lokasi bagus karena berada di tengah kota. Kondisi Hotel lumayanlah sesuai dengan tarif yang dibayarkan. Mau kemana-mana dekat. Free akses Wifi dengan speed yang rata-rata. Untuk menu sarapan termasuk bagus untuk kategori Hotel Melati. Ada air panas dan air dingin untuk mandi. Pelayanan staffnya ramah.
reviews.title: Lumayan di Tengah Kota

name: Hotel Raodah 2 Bontang
address: Jalan MT Haryono No.54 Depan Bank Syariah Mandiri, Bontang 75313 Indonesia

reviews.text: Had to book this Hotel because the other hotel was full and these two were the closest hotels to the site I had to visit. At that time there was only 1 room available, maybe I was just unlucky.. The room was located under stairs, it was very small, dark, lots of torn wallpaper, old window, and the worst is.. the bathroom. The pictures say it all.
reviews.title: Poor Room

reviews.text: Hotel ini di rekomendasikan oleh saudara saya karna selain murah harganya juga terjangkau jika melalui aplikasi travel online. Hanya saja ketika menginap terlalu banyak nyamuk dan laba laba besar bersarang di kamar mandi. Sarapan seadanya dan ada pengunjung yang hampir saja tidak mendapatkan sarapan. Seharusnya di peak season seperti lebaran pihak manajemen lebih memperhatikan kebersihan hotel dan ketersediaan sarapan untuk pengunjung supaya rate yang di dapatkan jauh lebih berguna kedepannya.
reviews.title: Hotel bontang

reviews.text: Hotel yang berada ditengah kota Bontang ini mudah dicari. Kesan pertama masuk hotel ini sangat minimalis. Desain kamar juga minimalis. Penerangan kamar terkesan kurang terang.. Kebersihan hotel haarus lebih diperhatikan. Menu sarapan sesuai standar hotel budget... Untuk kenyamanan tidur cukup tenang...
reviews.title: Ditengah Kota

name: Grand Mutiara Hotel
address: Km. 3 Jl. Arif Rahman Hakim, Bontang 75313 Indonesia

reviews.text: The staff was super helpful however the hotel was weird, seems very spooky and far from the city. The room was clean but there are more rooms than people who stays in it. If you looking for food you can forget it, its like in the middle of nowhere.
reviews.title: Not maintained

reviews.text: There was a SOE national meeting in Bontang and other hotel was fully occupied. So I had no better choice. This hotel was look older than its age. Not well maintained. The room wasn’t clean and the furnitures was very old. I didn’t have comfort sleep. The location also not in the city center. I didn’t take breakfast at the hotel. I lost my appetite.
reviews.title: Old and not maintained

reviews.text: Located in the suburbs of bontang city, presenting the nature view and suitable for stay in vacation especially in bontang east kalimantan cause near tourist attraction "kingkong". Hotel are presenting some facility like swimming pool, gym, and restaurant.
reviews.title: Parenting with ayah edy

reviews.text: Located far from city center, so it's quiet here. Actually this hotel is very nice, it's also has cozy feeling. Quite a modern hotel too. But its lack of maintenance. The veranda is dirty and the swimming pool leaking so guest can't use it
reviews.title: Nice and quiet hotel

reviews.text: I stayed here for 1 night. Checked in at 23.47 PM and had to check out early in the morning to continue our business trip. With that tight schedule, I wish I had a nice sleep. And my wish came true. The room was very neat, the staffs were so helpful. I highly recommend you to stay here if you go to Bontang. Very nice hotel.
reviews.title: Highly recommended

reviews.text:
I definitely will stay in this hotel each time I have trip to Bontang.  This is definitely the best one in the city, and they did some improvement too, on breakfast, on room service, and the room is now equipped with electric multiplug.

What disappoint me is: the wifi signal is still bad, it makes me difficult to work from the room. And most importantly, I just notice that the hotwater is scheduled until 9am for morning schedule and until around 7 pm for evening schedule.  It really is inconvenient since I often got back very late at the hotel.
reviews.title: Still love it

reviews.text:
Stayed at Oak Tree for a night over business trip to Bontang. Hotel is big with many rooms. Said to be a complex used for training athletics and has since been converted to a hotel. 

Room is clean, simple with basic necessities. Breakfast is standard Indonesian style with porridge, yellow rice, fried noodles. 

Good fresh morning dews as it is located up in high altitude. A decent hotel in a remote location.
reviews.title: Peace up at Oak Tree

reviews.text: I must say that this is definitely the best hotel in the city, don't bother to compare by staying at other hotel in the city center, you'll be disappointed.  It's located quite far from everything, restaurant, office complex, etc, the road access is bad, but you'll have a good sleep after an exhausting business meeting in this place. The room is clean, decent and relatively new, but I suggest you bring some snacks or instant drinks before getting here since the room doesn't equipped with water boiler, no coffee/ tea, and the room service mostly never have what they put on the menu.  Don't forget to bring your own multiplug as well since you'll get annoyed when you need to charge your cellphone and laptop at the same time, trust me, this hotel has the minimum facilities but again, the best in the city.
reviews.title: Best in the city

reviews.text:
Okay, I wrote the title in uppercase for a reason, it is indeed the best hotel in Bontang, and there's no doubt about it!

It's new, it's fresh, the design is modern-minimalist and it's far much better than it's only rival, the Bintang Sintuk Hotel.

The breakfast is just, well, just don't expect anything fancy. But the wifi is fast, the location is quite far, but Bontang is a small city anyway.

The TV, I didn't try..but every room come with it's private balcony and the AC is really cool so consider to 'manipulate' it somehow..
reviews.title: BEST HOTEL IN BONTANG, NO DOUBT!

reviews.text: setelah sekian lama ke bontang...hari ini saya ke bontang dalam rangka urusan pekerjaan, mencari penginapan yang terdekat dengan PKT , maka menginaplah di grand mutiara hotel ini alias oak tree hotel...kesan pertama : kamar besar akan tetapi ruangan lama serta waktu mandi ada kecoa yang entah dari mana muncul dan menempel di badan saya..suasana sepi dan jauh dari peradaban..saya merasa tertipu dengan foto hotelnya yang ada di google...mohon management hotel ini bisa meningkatkan lagi kebersihan , serta fasilitas hotelnya..
reviews.title: penilaian grand mutiara hotel alias oak tree hotel bontang

reviews.text:
Hotelnya sepi sekali, agak horor gitu, soalnya terlalu luas, dan Bontang kotanya juga sepi, pariwisata di Bontang kurang dioptimalkan, ya mungkin karena daerah Bontang adalah kawasan industri, sehingga sedikit visitor kesini, kecuali urusan bisnis.
Liftnya tidak berfungsi, jauh dari supermarket
reviews.title: Jauh dari peradaban

reviews.text: Salah satu hotel di Bontang Kalimantan Timur. Kamar mandinya terlalu sempit sih menurut aku. Lokasinya tepat di pinggir jalan yang saat ini sudah dicor. Ditempuh sekitar 3 jam dari Kota Samarinda Kalimantan Timur.
reviews.title: Luas areanya, sejuk dan tenang

reviews.text:
Hotel besar namun sepi.

1. AC gak berfungsi dengan baik
2. Siaran TV kurang baik
3. Yang paling parah dan akhirnya memutuskan untuk pindah hotel adalah sarapannya..sarapan tapi gak ada yg bisa dimakan..gimana itu jelasinnya..

Hotel ini dulunya hotel atlit PON Kaltim, setelah PON selesai bisa ditebak kan..tinggal kamar2 gelap yang tersisa..

reviews.text: kamar modern, pelayanan baik. tempatnya tenang jauh dari kejauhan. saya dulu pernah menjadi karyawan di hotel ini dan hanya 1 tahun, berharap hotel ini berada di tangan yg lebih ahli karna ini salah satu aset kota bontang, dan beberapa hasil foto dengan efek FISH EYE atau lensa cembung ini adalah HASIL FOTO SAYA. Skali lagi saya brharap hotel ini berada di tangan yang benar, makasi.
reviews.title: Pendapat dan pengalaman

reviews.text: nyari di internet, gambarnya sih bagus, pe sono, haduuh, jarang dirawat, dan terkesan serem, suasana tidak nyaman terasa ketika masuk ke lobby hotel, sungguh sangat disayangkan, karena sebenrnya banguna bagus, masuk ke kamar AC nya brisik banget, sarapan varian makannya kurang, dan yang seru lagi, kalau malem terdengar suara gaduh tapi ga kliatan orangnya
reviews.title: Hotel spooky

reviews.text: hotel ini jaraknya cukup jauh dari perkotaan dan berada di wilayah dekat pt.pupuk kaltim dan pelabuhan loktuan. hotel ini harganya lumayan terjangkau. pelayanannya bagus dan staf hotelnya ramah. anda harus coba.
reviews.title: hotel yang bagus

reviews.text: Bangunan hotel sangat luas dan besar. Fasilitas juga cukup lengkap dari kolam renang, r.meeting, dsb. Lokasi cukup jauh dari pusat kota. Kamar cukup baik tetapi perlu beberapa bagian yang harus diperbaiki. Kesimpulan hotel ini cukup baik
reviews.title: Oak Tree

reviews.text:
Mendengar kata Bontang, baru dua nama hotel yang terlintas di benak saya (sesuai pengalaman).Salah satunya adalah Oak Tree Hotel.
Hotel ini konon katanya adalah bekas asrama atlet sewaktu pelaksanaan PON (Pekan Olahraga Nasional) di Kalimantan Timur. Letaknya agak di pinggiran, tenang dan cenderung sepi dari keramaian. Jika dahulu jalan melewati depan hotel masih jalan biasa, saat ini jalan tersebut sudah dicor, jadi memudahkan akses/mobilisasi dari dan ke hotel. Hanya saja karena letaknya di pinggiran, yang menyebabkan transportasi agak sulit, kecuali jika memang kita membawa kendaraan sendiri. Bagian dalam hotel, berupa bangunan bertingkat, menyerupai rumah susun atau apartemen. 
Dilengkapi wifi, gym, kolam renang dengan pemandangan perbukitan Bontang. Dimana restorannya terletak di dekat kolam dengan latar tersebut tadi, lumayan memanjakan mata. 
Kamar cukup bersih,sarapan standar dan tidak terlalu banyak pilihan. 
Dinding lorong dihiasi dengan ornamen batik khas kalimantan yang dibingkai dan relief.
Dengan kelebihan dan kekurangannya, tetaplah hotel ini pilihan terbaik di Bontang
reviews.title: Pilihan terbaik di Bontang

photos.caption: Perbukitan bontang dan kolam yan dapat dipandang dari restoran

reviews.text:
Hotel terbaik di Bontang, kl pertimbangan harga dan kenyamanan,, kamar luas, dan nyaman,, harga jauh murah dibandingkan satu hotel yang cukup terkenal disini, tetapi setelah melihat kamar masing2 saya pilih hotel ini untuk yang terbaik di Bontang,,, 
Kl ndak percaya keliling aja, bandingkan yg lain... Kelemahannya memang jauh dari pusat kota,, tp hotel yg dekat pusat kota semuanya tipe melati prendd..
reviews.title: Hotel terbaik di Bontang,,

reviews.text: Lokasinya yang lumayan jauh dari kota, membuat hotel ini bagus untuk anda yang mencari ketenangan. Akses jalan menuju hotel juga sudah diperbaiki. Pelayanan hotel yang beberapa tahun lalu bekas wisma atlet ini juga sangat responsif. Makanannya enak-enak.
reviews.title: Bagus untuk mencari ketenangan

name: Akbar Hotel
address: Jln. Imam Bonjol No. 65, Bontang 75311 Indonesia

reviews.text:
Friendly staff, spacious rooms, free wifi, are the pros of staying. The hotel is located in a strategic location near kenari water park. Also the price is low, average value for money. 

Food options are minimum, you can expect only Indonesian food here with little options but good for taste buds.
reviews.title: Budget hotel

reviews.text:
well, nothing much to tell about the hotel,,the hotel need some renovation in all areas..especially the room,,a lot if mosquitos and really need to improve about the cleanliness,,
the room actually big but really need a lot improvement,,well, as far i know, this is family hotel,,thats why it seems they dont really care about to di some changing.
reviews.title: nothing much

reviews.text:
Ini merupakan kesempatan pertama kali menginap di hotel ini. Kesan pertama, hotel ini biasa saja, tetapi ketika masuk ke kamar, cukup kaget dengan kamar yang luas. Dengan dua tempat tidur yang terdapat di kamar, terasa masih ada ruang kosong yang luas. Hanya saja, bangunannya terkesan usang.
Sarapan pagi yang disajikan, terkesan apa adanya, hanya ada 1 menu, tanpa pilihan lain.
Nilai lebih dari hotel ini adalah lokasinya mudah diakses dan tarifnya pun relatif murah
reviews.title: Biasa saja, tidak ada yang istimewa

reviews.text: tgl 11-13 april perjalanan dinas ke bontang, menginap di hotel ini, dengan kamar tipe superior per malam Rp 330.000,- (include tax). tergolong hotel yang lama, kamar cukup luas, ac standar, parkir luas, memang perlu renovasi untuk tampilannya. receptionist cuma 1 orang, padahal hotelnya lumayan banyak kamar. sarapan lumayan lah.
reviews.title: Hotel Murah

reviews.text: Nilai plus hotel ini lokasinya yang strategis...gampang cari makan...kualitas kamar standart kelas melati..ada air hangat...wifi bisa diakses dari kamar....sarapan biasa aja......recommended kalo budget hotel lg terbatas...
reviews.title: Biasa aja...untuk kelas melati..

name: Hotel Gembira
address: Jl. Hayam Wuruk No. 7-9, Bontang Indonesia

reviews.text:
Located in the center of Bontang city, the hotel was quite good for standart 2-3 stars hotel. But it’s better if you choose the new building in the front, it’s less noise because there’s a karaoke bar in the back of the hotel that connected to the old building.

The room was standard and clean, A/C work well and the water heater also. But there’s no hairdryer here, so bring your own.

The good things for me is you can order beer here and drink it in the lobby, they have bintang and prost for standard price around 30-35k.
reviews.title: Nice city hotel

reviews.text:
Awalnya agak underestimate tapi begitu checkin semua cukup ok. Proses checkin cepat, staff ya standard hotel melati lah. Tapi kamar sangat luas ( bagunan baru depan ) bersih begitu juga dengan kamar mandinya. AC dingin, perlengkapan kamar juga lengkap seperti handuk, perlengkapan mandi, air mineral, gula kopi teh. Breakfast lumayan yg saya kaget karena ada egg stationnya.
Overall buat saya rekomend hotel di Bontang
reviews.title: Sedang

reviews.text:
Hotel Melati tapi lebih nyaman dari hotel Bintang yang ada di kota Bontang.
Kamar luas dan bersih, stafnya ramah, breakfasnya enak.
Lokasi strategis, dekat ke PT Badak LNG, banyak penjual makanan jika malam.
Untuk menginap di Bontang hotel Gembira  sy rekomendasikan.
reviews.title: Terbaik di Bontang

reviews.text:
Hotel ini mmg bukan hotel bintang, hanya hotel kelas melati, namun dibandingkan dengan hotel berbintang di kota Bontang, hotel ini ttp yang terbaik.
Kamar luas dan bersih, kamar mandi bersih, pelayanan hotel bagus serta breakfast yang cukup baik san enak.
Dengan harga yang lebih murah di bandingkan hotel bintang jelas hotel gembira menjadi pilihan terbaik jika kita menginap di kota Bontang
reviews.title: Pilihan terbaik di Bontang

reviews.text:
Positifnya adalah lokasinya yang berada di tengah kota. 
Namun hotel ini cukup minimalis, AC tidak terlalu dingin, kebersihan yang masih perlu ditingkatkan. Sprei dan handuk tidak terlalu bersih. Makanan juga sangat-sangat sederhana. Kebetulan saya menginap waktu itu saat sedang bulan puasa, jadi saya tidak sarapan namun, makan sahur. Makanan sahur yang tersedia hanyalah nasi putih dengan telur bulat dan mie goreng serta kerupuk. Dengan minuma kopi dan atau teh hangat. Sangat minim. 
Jadi jika masih ada pilihan yang lain, sepertinya akan mending untuk memilih tempat menginap yang lain.
reviews.title: Biasa cenderung ke minimal

name: Okra Leaf Guest House
address: Jl. DI Panjaitan RT 27 No..4, Bontang Indonesia

reviews.text: pelayanannya bagus,hommy,tersedia makan pagi juga.puas sekali menginap di hotel ini.di banding yang lain ini tempat terbaik untuk menginap di bontang.pembelian bisa melalui online juga.sangat memudahkan.

reviews.text: Guest House yang berada dikota bontang ini mudah dijangkau. Tempat yang tenang untuk beristirahat. Pelayanan yang ramah. Kebersihan yang terjaga.. Tempat sarapan yang berada dibelakang bangunan sangat cocok untuk santai.. Dekat dengan pusat kota..

name: Bintang Sintuk Hotel
address: Jl. Urea, PT. Pupuk Kaltim Kaltim Bontang Golf Area, Bontang 75311 Indonesia

reviews.text: Located in city of Bontang, 2 hours north side from Samarinda, the capital city of Kalimantan Timur province, Indonesia. The hotel is very nice and confortable for travellers an tourism for explore the tropical forest of Borneo.
reviews.title: Bintang Sintuk hotel, the Indonesia cottage

reviews.text: The room was very old and the hotel seems to be very old. It has a good facility including Golf Course just next to it. Food was okay nothing spectacular. Staff was nice and the hotel has some what a good view.
reviews.title: Very old

reviews.text: Not worth. Quite expensive for what you get. Old hotel, poor maintenance, stain all over the room. This is the biggest hotel in town, with pool, golf, and resort style. Could be better if managed with professional hotel management.
reviews.title: Big hotel but not the best

reviews.text:
Bontang is a small city although there are two huge national-scale companies here. In fact Bontang was established and built as the result of those two companies operating here. Bontang itself is not a tourist attraction city. Most people are here for work, business trip or trade.

That is why not many hotels are found here. Bintang Sintuk Hotel is a 3-stars hotel and for many years remain the only 3-stars hotel in Bontang. Built in the 80s I think.

The service (room and food) is average. Room is its best and i have no complaints. However the food is very average. I was suprised when the quality of breakfast and room service were below my expectation. I’ve been to many 3-stars hotels in Indonesia and it is not that difficult to make a decent food. That is why i couldn’t understand Bintang Sintuk couldn’t even make a good omelette, sauteed sausage, and sauteed garlic potato.

Didn’t use their meeting rooms, so i couldn’t make any comments.

Apart from their status as a 3-stars hotel, they do have a very nice swimming pool with nice view of golf field. However the pool is not that private as it is located next to breakfast area.
reviews.title: Not much but still it is the best hotel today in Bontang

reviews.text:
Ten years ago I visited this city many times and this hotel was the best one. After ten years my friend still recommended this hotel. But, everything seems remain the same. The hotel and room looks very old and less maintained. The curtain was torn in several parts. Breakfast was very standard. But anyway I still could sleep comfortly. The best part of this hotel, I think was the swimming pool.
Anyway, this is a small city and its economy really depend on PKT and LNG. Current hotel supply is more than enough. I didn’t expect to get better hotel here.
reviews.title: Didn’t expect more

reviews.text: I stayed here for a night. The room was clean. Breakfast had some Indonesian and western menu. The taste was ok. The view from the restaurant was a combination of forest and sea. Unfortunately I needed to walk too far to the swimming pool. One suggestion: toilet near the lobby need to be cleaned.
reviews.title: I like the view from the restaurant

reviews.text:
Bontang... Pupuk Kaltim and Badak LNG country.  That’s pretty much all that people come here for.  Bintang Sintuk Hotel is probably the only hotel in the area that has the most rooms.  Golf course and olympic size pool (at least I think it is).  Food is mediocre and breakfast buffet is nothing to right home about.  Coffee is better off serving Kapal Api or similar instead of the coffee currently served.  

Rooms are “ok” and staff are all very welcoming and pleasant.  

Getting around is pretty easy and there is not much traffic around the town of Bontang.
reviews.title: It is what it is... no bells and whistles

reviews.text: I believe all reviews here give an accurate description of this hotel. For the location it is a reasonable hotel. I didn't get to check out any of the facilities but did have a walk around the golf course a couple of times. The rooms were acceptable although the curtains didn't quite shut properly and the Aircon unit outside the window was quite noisy. I slept reasonably well regardless. Rooms were clean although could do with some touch ups here and there. Staff were all pleasant and helpful. One thing I did notice and I'm particularly sensitive to is that I found the level of MSG quite high in some dishes as I was very thirsty after eating breakfast and lunch at the restaurant. I think next time I would need to request less. On the whole a reasonable stay and would go again.
reviews.title: Few nights in Bontang

reviews.text: When you must have business trip to Bontang, you don't really have choice to spend the night. Even President Jokowi spent night in this hotel. This hotel is little bit spooky, but..hey you need adrenalin at least once in your life. Breakfast quite standard and also the service. But what I notice their employees have great smile. So..at least I feel welcome to their hotel. If you kind of person who really clean and hygenis, I suggest you lower your standard a little bit first, then you can survive.
reviews.title: No Choice

reviews.text: I stayed frequently in this hotel since the last 8 months. This hotel has been a while, located in the complex of Pupuk Kaltim, surrounded by golf course. There are 2 or 3 tennis court, and olympic swimming pool. There are park near the hotel if you want to take a walk or jogging. You will need a ride to take you to nearest Bontang stores, market, restaurant, etc.
reviews.title: Hotel within Golf Course

photos.caption: View to golf course and the bay

reviews.text: The property is located in the center of 18 holes Sintuk Golf Course in Bontang. The view is awesome, green landscape with Pupuk Kaltim Plants and Beach as background. Suggest to select Deluxe Room if you stay here, you will get that beach view, otherwise you only get view of parking area :-)
reviews.title: Hotel with the best view in Bontang

reviews.text: Stayed there for a week and found that the hotel is fairly under maintained. The room I was in felt like it hasn't been used for a year. It was spacious and the bed was comfortable. Despite that, the hotel have a few extra facilities such as the golf course, driving range and 2 swimming pools. Though this hotel has it shortfalls, the scenery over looking the golf course, ocean wide and the plant refinery justified to it's claim of the best hotel in East Kalimantan.
reviews.title: 3 Bintang Hotel

reviews.text:
I stayed at this hotel for 2 months. Only good hotel in the area. Rooms are ok. Old property and needs lots of renovation. Food is not great but you survive.

Its inside a golf course and you are stuck as you cannot go out. Generally a hotel for people visiting the lng or fertilizer plants.

Nothing much and food in the market is better.
reviews.title: 2 months stay

reviews.text: Rooms are placed amongst the spacious green garden. Although it is located just near the petrochemical industry plant, it is a good place to rest after about 150 miles journey from Sepinggan Airport. Some area in Bontang are still green covered with artificial forests.
reviews.title: Spacious exterior and interior.

reviews.text: Old and tired but very convinience to the industrial complex so it suited to my travel purpose and I think it's still the best choice in Bontang. The surrounding was beautiful, next to golf course overlooking to the port and petrochem plants. The wifi connection in the room was bit frustating but it worked okay in the lobby area.
reviews.title: Tired but still the best choice in Bontang

reviews.text: Bontang is a small, neat, and clean city. This hotel is one of a main feature in this city. It must have been one of the best hotels in it's time. It now needs upgrade, especially in its interior so to lessen the shabiness. It still has potential to grow to a better hotel since they have a good chef, nice personnels, good location, beautiful golf course, and an olympic size swimming pool.
reviews.title: A nice hotel from the past

reviews.title: Average 3 star Hotel

reviews.text:
They say it is the best hotel in Bontang. If so, there are great opportunities for hotel business.
The area around the hotel is very big. Make sure you walk around outside the main building to enjoy the surrounding. 
The hotel itself is old, and even from outside it already looks rather poorly maintained. 
The room is big but some insects crawl on top of my blanket. Worst of all is the internet. After calling the staff a few times, they give me some login numbers and passwords that do not work. 
The staff are friendly but you can feel that they are not being trained to treat customers more than usual politeness
reviews.title: unimpressive stay

reviews.text: Not really as good as their name ........I think it's very old hotel with poor maintenance....... Need to improved a lot.... The location is really nice...away from city noise.....ask for the east view toward the golf field..... U gonna like it.......
reviews.title: The call it bintang

reviews.text:
Got a golf view room, the mangroves along the bay are beautiful. Unfortunately the hotel looks old and tired. Room size is OK, but need to be refreshed. Windows are not sealed well, and its' glasses are dirty. No wifi in the room, by plug cable instead.
Room cleanliness is far below the 3 stars hotel standard. 
The rate is too expensive for this kind of room.
reviews.title: Need to maintain the hotel properly

reviews.title: Cozy but needs attention

reviews.text: Bungalows type hotel......near industrial area....it's look good but need renovation, the hotel is really old..... It was one of best hotel in town........Swimming pool is small .... The foods are average...... Far from town.........
reviews.title: Old hotel

reviews.text:
Stay 1 night in this hotel. A hotel with vast area and bungalow model. Actually good hotel, but old one and need renovation.
Very quiet and let you have good sleep.
Not too much TV channel option or entertainment, but that will let you rest all night.
reviews.title: Quiet and cozy place to stay in town

reviews.text: I stayed here by accident as my client forgot to book me into the good hotel (this put me in a bad mood from the start).  I spent two nights here.  I understand I did not get a good room as hotel rooms in Bontang were at a premium at the time.  The rooms are basically built of plywood and have seen better days.  The short list of things wrong with my room: phone didn't work, internet connection broken (very important as I couldn't get a mobile signal and I wasn't where I was supposed to be) no remote control for the aircon and I could not set it to a cool enough temperature (this was fixed for the 2nd night), the water cooler didn't (it did give hot water but I had no tea or coffee), electric sockets hanging from the walls, shower room dirty.
reviews.title: Cheap and but nothing works

reviews.text: Termasuk hotel tua dikota bontang, seluruh bangunan dibuat dari kayu ulin, kayu khas kalimantan, dengan bentuk rumah panggung semakin menambah keunikan hotel ini. Tapi sayang sekali, karena sangat minim perawatan dan interior yang sangat kuno, tempat tidur, bathtub, sofa semuanya tua, seharusnya sudah waktunya dilakukan peremajaan. Kolam renang tersedia, cukup lumayanlah untuk kota kecil sekelas bontang. Restoran untuk sarapannya sangat membosankan dengan menu yang itu2 saja. Tapi anda bisa memesan makanan yang tersedi dimenu karena rasanya cukup lezat.
